[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     55[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m Change the SMS pattern in the pseudocode and the prose to the "notification-plus-portal-link" model: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mrendered["sms_messages"] = [localize("Your after-visit summary is ready. Open it in the patient portal: {portal_link}", patient_prefs.language)][38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m. No clinical content in the SMS payload.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     56[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m If direct-to-SMS clinical content is retained as a pattern (some practices support it), add an explicit section in "Why This Isn't Production-Ready" titled "SMS and PHI" that names the consent requirement, the lack of end-to-end encryption on SMS, the content-minimization best practice, and the jurisdiction-specific overlays. Add a prerequisite check in Step 7 pseudocode: [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mIF "sms" in patient_prefs.delivery_channels AND patient_prefs.sms_phi_consent != "granted": fall back to notification-plus-link pattern.[38;2;163;190;140m`[K
