[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    164[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The sample summary contains roughly 20+ specific claims (atrial fibrillation diagnosis, stroke-risk framing, apixaban name, dose, timing, start instruction, CBC/kidney-check instruction, result-delivery phrasing, follow-up date and time, follow-up clinician, full call-911 warning list, full call-during-day list, three lifestyle instructions, practice phone number, practice hours). The provenance list in the JSON contains only 5 entries. For a recipe that teaches "every specific claim must trace to source," the showcase output models an incomplete trace. A reader following this pattern would build a validator that catches only 5 of the 20+ claims the model actually made, which misses the whole point of the architecture.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    165[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Expand the [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mfactual_claims[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m array in the sample output to enumerate the full set of specific claims with source-field paths: diagnoses[0] for the atrial fibrillation name, warning_signs[[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m] for each bleeding-warning item, education_topics[[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m] or lifestyle_instructions[[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m] for "Tell any doctor or dentist...", "Avoid contact sports...", and similar, practice_info for the phone number and hours, and so on. A dozen-plus entries, not five. Alternatively, add a note beneath the sample: "The [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mfactual_claims[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;180;142;173m array in this sample is abbreviated for readability. A production validator enumerates every specific claim, typically 15-30 per AVS."[K
